[ProMED-mail has posted multiple reports of scrub typhus in several Indian states in the past, especially since 2011. For background information, see ProMED-mail post Scrub typhus - India (05): background 20111208.3546.

Maps of India can be seen at http://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/india/india-political-map.htm and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5211944,62230.
Imphal West district, with a population of 514 683 residents, is the most populous district of the 16 districts of Manipur state in northeastern India (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imphal_West_district). Manipur is bounded by Nagaland to the north, Mizoram to the south, Assam to the west, and Myanmar to the east (http://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/manipur/manipur.htm). The city of Imphal is the capital of Manipur. A map showing the location of Imphal can be found at https://www.google.com/maps/place/Imphal,+Manipur,+India. - Mod.ML]
